omputational Fluid Dynamics</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/szaghi/OFF/tree/testing\">OFF</a> - Open source Finite volume Fluid dynamics code.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-02-02T11:27:59.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"rabbiabram/awesome-fortran","categoryHTML":"<h2>Fortran Websites</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://fortranwiki.org/fortran/show/HomePage\">Fortran WIKI</a> - An open venue for discussing all aspects of the Fortran programming language and scientific computing.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-02-02T11:27:59.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"prakhar1989/awesome-courses","categoryHTML":"<h2>Courses</h2><h3>Systems</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://comp.uark.edu/~wingning/csce3613/csce3613.html\">CSCE 3613</a> <strong>Operating Systems</strong> <em>University of Arkansas (Fayetteville)</em> <img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f4bb.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" alt=\"Assignments\" title=\"Assignments\"> <img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f4dd.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" alt=\"Lecture Notes\" title=\"Lecture Notes\"><img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f4da.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" alt=\"Readings\" title=\"Readings\">\t- An introduction to operating systems including topics in system structures, process management, storage management, files, distributed systems, and case studies.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://comp.uark.edu/~wingning/csce3613/CSCE3613.pdf\">Syllabus</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://comp.uark.edu/~wingning/csce3613/Homework3613.html\">Assignments</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://comp.uark.edu/~wingning/csce3613/CourseNote3613.html\">Lecture Notes</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://comp.uark.edu/~wingning/csce3613/Link3613.html\">Readings</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2015-02-02T10:38:46.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"prakhar1989/awesome-courses","categoryHTML":"<h2>Courses</h2><h3>Systems</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://compsci.hunter.cuny.edu/~sweiss/course_materials/csci360/csci360_f14.php\">CSCI 360</a> <strong>Computer Architecture 3</strong> <em>CUNY Hunter College</em> <img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f4bb.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" alt=\"Assignments\" title=\"Assignments\"> <img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f4dd.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" alt=\"Lecture Notes\" title=\"Lecture Notes\">\n<ul>\n<li>A course that covers cache design, buses, memory hierarchies, processor-peripheral interfaces, and multiprocessors, including GPUs.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2015-02-02T10:38:46.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"prakhar1989/awesome-courses","categoryHTML":"<h2>Courses</h2><h3>Algorithms</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www-scf.usc.edu/~csci104/20142/lectures/\">CSCI 104</a> <strong>Data Structures and Object Oriented Design</strong> <img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f4bb.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" alt=\"Assignments\" title=\"Assignments\"> <img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f4dd.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" alt=\"Lecture Notes\" title=\"Lecture Notes\"> <em>University of Southern California (USC)</em>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://www-scf.usc.edu/~csci104/20142/lectures\">Lectures</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www-scf.usc.edu/~csci104/20142/labs\">Labs</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www-scf.usc.edu/~csci104/20142/assignments/\">Assignments</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www-scf.usc.edu/~csci104/20142/resources.html\">Additional Resources</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2015-02-02T01:02:11.000Z"}]}},"pageContext":{"type":"day","from":1422835200000,"to":1422921599999,"previousId":"2015-02-03","nextId":"2015-02-01","nextName":"Feb 1st, 2015","previousName":"Feb 3rd, 2015"}},"staticQueryHashes":["228695001","2744905544","4035379035"]}